name: breast papillary carcinoma
definition: A breast carcinoma that is characterized by the presence of arborescent fibrovascular stalks lined by epithelial cells, grossly forming a circumscribed mass. [url:https\://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3244819/]

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a Phase I clinical trial, a patient with ER-positive, ERBB2 (HER2)-negative papillary breast carcinoma harboring AKT1 E17K had a sustained partial response to AZD5363 (PMID: 26351323).

references.title: Tumors with AKT1E17K Mutations Are Rational Targets for Single Agent or Combination Therapy with AKT Inhibitors.
